# Execution stack

Manages `turbo exec`, the execution order of other scripts, and the main timer.

**!!! Because of the way `turbo exec` works, it can mess with your existing scripts, make sure to disable any other script that has an impulse while you use these scripts !!!**

Specifically, scripts that hit the end of their code won't exit normally, but
will repeat the last line for many iterations before (eventually) exiting when
the frame updates. Because of this, it is safest to always end `turbo exec`
scripts with `wait(0.)` or `goto(99)` or something else that is a no-op.

Also, be aware that these scripts (intentionally) hide global variables in the
debug overlay. If you have a variable you wish to display, it's advised you
set it in `load global display`, before the last line.
